I was a little apprehensive to write about this dream... but its really itching at me so I decided to choose the journal with the least amount of readership... and one that isn't wired to stalkerbook.

So interestingly enough I have had a dream quite similar to this in high school, a little different... a little less intense... and a different ... mentor I guess you would say?

So my dream is I'm getting up early for today... I guess I actually skipped work.. and it was actually semi decent weather outside... unfortunately.. I was headed to Stephen's class to take a test (the same test I'm actually taking today)... I was headed straight there until Dave Swen. stopped me in the street right outside of the student center.. and he asks "Audrey do you have a few moments so we can talk"  so I.. thinking it was AFRC related say "Sure"  He immediately starts talking... saying he's worried and he brought some people to talk to me.  These two guys in semi-casual clothes with name tags... but not fancy name tags... but sticker ones... and Dave tells me "I know what you have been doing..."  I start thinking when the last time I had done it... In my dream.. I dreamt (yes i dreamed in a dream) that I had done it in some sort of office place.. but I looked at my arms and saw nothing... I started to panic some... thinking that something like this would get me kicked out of everything... The two blockheads start asking me questions and have this device and are running it along my skin while also checking my pulse.. to see if I get some sort of through or something.. I keep thinking that I'm so freaking nervous that the thing is making my heart race... this is where the dream gets a little sketchy and the next thing I know the guy is taking me to the clinic (which sucks)... and then I'm not sure what happens... all I know is that the whole time i was nervous cause I didn't think Stephen would let me makeup the test...

very confusing dream but I needed to write it down... I still feel weird about it...but what can you do....  The one in high school was mostly just my physics teacher talking to me about it... but I find both of these men high on my list of good people... so who knows...


rain

I sit in the place that gives me chills... and i write... nonsensical words... nonstop....silliness... gazing gradient gargantuan giants...

ok thats sorta out of my system

So i decided its update time... due to the fact I want to look like I am accomplishing something... when in reality.. I am not.

So I feel like this week will be busy again... but not kill me busy like last week... I still need to get my hands upon something that will help me organize my life... like a personal agenda... boo to being unorganized... poor and unorganized...I just need to start writing things on my hand again... like the good ol high school days...but alas... i rarely carry a pen... and if i do it usually ends up exploding in my sac a dos... c'est la vie...

Speaking of french.. I feel like my mind is severely crowded with french... french... and more french... this is the most work I have done in french in a long time... I guess having two 3or4xxx classes doesnt help... but whatever.. its still good... just a lot more work than I am used to... Plus its hard enough when I prioritize biology as my number 1... and choosing between the two... then french... eeeech... then all the non school... schooly extracurricular things.... maaaaaaaaan... plus figuring out what I want to do next year... I'm stuck inbetween grad school and the peace corps... both having several pros... and a few cons... its the decision thats the hardest thing... and piecing my life together... So much... so many feelings... gahhhhhhhhhh

but this newest option has been interesting me more and more each time i think about it, but I am trying to arrange a visit to find out for sure.  It would doing some more duck nesting research... which would be really interesting... haha the con you ask?  Living in the twin cities... seriously... morris has made me wimped out on living in the big city.. Im spoiled in this small town atmosphere....BOO

but... what do you do... So I'm continuing to work on my Peace Corps application while also arranging meetings with different grad school professors to try to get grad school information.  This probably means I should also start thinking about signing up for the GRE...


Matt says its time to learn... I guess I am done here... but... someday we can talk again... maybe face to face...  you can find me in the ol TMC

I've been an emotional nightmare since school started that I haven't found it in me to update.  I am finally feeling the need to become independent again.  I decided to stop taking any sort of shit from customers at work, any sort of shit from other people... and I just plan to live contently?

Anyways

So school has started and I feel more busy than I could have imagined.  I'm working about 20 hours a week and did receive the chair position on the committee I am on.  I finished/presented my senior seminar two weeks ago, and I feel happy that that stress is not in my life anymore.  But for some reason I feel that I haven't really found any extra time during the week.  I fell a little behind in French Class but I am slowly catching up.

I am enjoying the new living situation, though I currently never seem to be home except for on weekends... and it still seems hard to see the roomies. 

I haven't been able to volunteer as much as I would like because I have been so busy (which is no excuse, but what can you do?) 

Ever since school started I have been wanting to go home and see friends and family.  Unfortunately I still have to wait another 20 days until I can do that.  But it will be a glorious time when it does happen.  I am just hoping we don't get a freak snowstorm at that time to delay my trip home.  Luckily enough there have been enough activities every weekend to keep my mind off of home.  This weekend is the jazz concerts, next weekend is HomeKUMMing concert, weekend after that I should be headed home!

This past Friday, I went to SDSU to visit with a professor there about grad school.  Unfortunately her research focuses on soybeans and I would prefer other types of ecology.  This sort of changes my plans for next year.
Sara has someone I can talk to at the UM tc about duck research... Or the Peace Corps (my application is finished except for a few essays), or an apprenticeship to teach English in France, or find some company that will pay for culinary school for me if I promise to work for them.

So right now I am lost, lost, lost

I don't even know how to write about the rest.  I've talked with a few friends about stuff.  But I don't know... suck it up or something?

Anyways I suppose I should study some since I have both my PLant Bio and Vert Nat Hist tests this week, Plus a translation

Followed by a paper on some topic of french medieval history... due next week....\

So I am alive, and I guess that counts for something...

well as soon as break is about to end.. it finally gets interesting...


but that's supposed to happen...

I got to work two weeks at good ol wendys... which was horrible the first week, working with a manager that is hypocritical and rips people apart for little things that are ridiculous... So I was not happy to be back...But I noticed I got another raise... Money is a hard thing to judge by... you don't want to be greedy... and you want to be able to pay the bills and live comfortably.. the question is.. is it worth it?

so Im still pondering the question and trying to figure out how this summer will be working for me....

but I really don't want to think about that now...

I've gone through so many thought processes this break... Some I will never understand.. and some I qill just choose to not understand....

But I feel like the conclusion is what I want... its like everything I had was already there... it just needed to be polished up a bit... I can't necessarily say I feel stupid... i didn't do anything..... its just the thought I suppose...


But it feels good to know...

I have changed a lot....

my first email account... has over 700 unread messages... granted most of it is spam... and it has accumulated to the extreme because of my neglect to delete things..I just have this feeling to delete it... cut out a fragment of an old self that doesn't exist anymore...but I have messages in there since the beginning... I have saved emails of conversations with friends... emails with a friend that made a small impact in my life who i never speak to anymore...emails from my father that I could just never get around to deleting...

so who knows if I will ever get rid of it... I just have this hard time with getting rid of things like that...

I rarely read the old messages... but there has been a few times.. when falling back on them has helped me grow...

haha plus Im waiting for an email from myself that comes at 2050? I think... a time capsule sort of thing.. I should have made a copy for myself.. so i could read it now.. But i guess there's no fun in that when i keep reminding myself about myself from a couple years back... (annoying repetition)

AHHH I just feel completely different now....


good... bad?  WHo knows... its just one of those things that you can't help but notice...

I sometimes feel that maybe my friends don't like the different me... maybe they don't notice...

I feel it... and sometimes Im not sure if I like it...

just this break ive grown up.. and moved on from things that were weighing me down... it feels good.. but I still find the future scary... maybe scarier than before...

but that could be because its one day closer...
